title: MEGA HERACROSS
body:
According to the Ultra Sun Pokedex, Mega Heracross can lift 500 times its own weight. Mega Heracross weighs 62,5 KG. 62,5 times 500 is 31250 KG. Wailord weighs 398 KG. 31250 KG divided by 398 is 78. 

So! If my math is correct, Mega Heracross should be able to lift 78 Wailord at the same time.

blog.name: inikavulpixelreviews
blog.title: Let's Talk About Pokemon!
blog.description:
Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Sewaddle Family
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Sewaddle Family
body:
540: Sewaddle

We briefly had another dip, but now we’re getting flung right back into the good stuff full-force. And we FINALLY have our obligatory caterpillar line! Even if it doesn’t evolve the way you think it would.

But Sewaddle is like. Actually, objectively, and subjectively speaking, entirely too adorable. It should be illegal. Just LOOK. What a cute face it has!! And not only that, it’s wearing a little baby bonnet made of leaves its mother Leavanny made for it!!! And being the caterpillar-esque creature that it is, it even looks like it’s chewed on that very bonnet like the naughty, misbehaving infant that it is. HNNNNGH. OUCH. It’s so adorable it’s physically bringing me pain.

Personal Score: 9/10

HHHH

541: Swadloon

Going through the whole rigamarole here aren’t we? From the only baby I’ll ever call adorable to an awkward, anti-social teenager type of stage. Either that or it’s me come winter time. While maybe not as stomach-sickeningly cute as Sewaddle, it’s still a fun design that’s a neat take on the “cocoon” stage of these Pokemon. And a fun way around the weird problem with how technically this line shouldn’t be caterpillar-into-cocoon-into-whatever, but it wound up that way anyhow.

Personal Score: 8/10

Don’t be such a grouch!

542: Leavanny

Surprisingly enough, this Gen’s Caterpie equivalent doesn’t become a pretty butterfly or even a moth, but rather a leaf insect…? Leaf insects are the type of bugs that have a nymph stage rather than going through metamorphosis, but sure. It’s Pokemon, it’s gotten away with weirder inaccuracies.

Leavanny goes back to being a cute, humanoid bug that thankfully isn’t too anthropomorphised to not look weird. There’s lots of segments and parts awkwardly pinching in to a really small point, but it never looks outright awful. That’s about all I can criticize though, the rest of the design is very nice and not much wrong about it offends that badly.

As aforementioned, Leavanny is one of the most fashion-savvy Pokemon out there. It takes leaves and weaves clothing out of them using its cutter arms and silk, made for its Sewaddle and Swadloon children. It even does this for any small Pokemon it may find. That’s just too precious. I can’t take it.

Personal Score: 9/10

I love leaf-mom.

Overall:

Arguably one of the cutest lines out there to date.

[Archive]
